              <tr>
                <td width="614" valign="top"><p>Hotel location for    the International Regulators Offshore Safety Conference in 2007 chosen for    the informal atmosphere (and Florida for the warm weather!). The theme chosen    by MMS was discussed and altered. A more detailed description of the theme    will be given on the IRF website to include, amongst others, performance and    the reputation of the industry amongst potential young employees. A list of    purposes for the 2007 meeting was given and discussed and the predicted    budget given. The members agreed not to seek industry sponsorships. Consensus    was reached on a fee of no more than $700 p.p. for the meeting with a    separate reduced fee for partners. A link to the registration for will be    posted on the website. The issue of VIPs (e.g., government, labour, industry)    as key note speakers for the meeting was discussed.<br />
                  -----------------------------------------------------------</p>
                    <p>Ian Whewell gave a    presentation on the same subject, with an overview of the proposed programme    for the meeting containing some key points for discussion, including number    of participants and the exclusion/inclusion of academic representation. There    was agreement that the key note speakers should be spread out over the    programme.<br />
